main event: An object observed at Whiteman AFB, Missouri on 24 September 1965 is concluded to be a satellite.
interesting points: The object was observed as a very bright, white light in the sky for approximately 15 minutes,The object's movement was initially erratic before it proceeded in a smooth, steady course,It was round in shape and approximately the size of a quarter at arm's length,No audible sound was detected during the sighting,The observers included two airmen from the 351st Combat Defense Squadron, considered reliable.
sighted object: a bright white light in the sky
witness description: A2C Charles McBrayer and A3C John L. Bolding from the 351st Combat Defense Squadron
